.TH "filemap_write_and_wait_range" 9 "filemap_write_and_wait_range" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
filemap_write_and_wait_range \- write out & wait on a file range
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" filemap_write_and_wait_range
.BI "(struct address_space *mapping "  ","
.BI "loff_t lstart "  ","
.BI "loff_t lend "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mapping" 12
the address_space for the pages
.IP "lstart" 12
offset in bytes where the range starts
.IP "lend" 12
offset in bytes where the range ends (inclusive)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Write out and wait upon file offsets lstart->lend, inclusive.

Note that \fIlend\fP is inclusive (describes the last byte to be written) so
that this function can be used to write to the very end-of-file (end = -1).
.SH "RETURN"
error status of the address space.
